nformatica Cloud Data Masking** for anonymization.  \n2. Adopt **Informatica Advanced Masking Solution** to protect sensitive data.  \n3. Partner with **securiti.ai** (via Informatica) to monitor unauthorized access.  \n4. Extend log retention to 1+ years per DPDP Section 6(1)(e).  \n\n---\n\n### 4. Data Breach Notification (16.7%)  \n**Risk Level**: Critical  \n**Implications**: Missed 72-hour reporting windows may trigger penalties.  \n\n**Action Items**:  \n1. Develop a breach notification plan with predefined templates.  \n2. Automate alerts to ensure timely reporting.  \n\n---\n\n### 5. Children’s Data Protection (0.0%)  \n**Risk Level**: Critical  \n**Implications**: Processing children’s data without parental consent violates DPDP Section 10.  \n\n**Action Items**:  \n1. Implement multi-factor authentication for parental consent.  \n2. Build age-verification tools using **Informatica Cloud Data Quality**.  \n\n---\n\n### 6. Cross-Border Data Transfers (33.3%)  \n**Risk Level**: High  \n**Implications**: Unrestricted data flows outside India risk non-compliance with DPDP Section 12(4).  \n\n**Action Items**:  \n1. Use **Informatica Cloud Data Governance Catalog** to enforce location-based policies.  \n2. Restrict access to personal data from unauthorized jurisdictions.  \n\n---\n\n### 7. Documentation & Compliance (40.0%)  \n**Risk Level**: Medium  \n**Implications**: Lack of audit trails may hinder accountability.  \n\n**Action Items**:  \n1. Automate documentation with **Informatica Enterprise Data Catalog**.  \n2. Appoint a Data Protection Officer (DPO) per DPDP Section 9.  \n\n---\n\n## Strategic Recommendations  \n1. **Prioritize High-Risk Areas**: Focus on breach notification, children’s data, and security controls.  \n2. **Leverage Informatica Solutions**:  \n   - **Data Discovery**: **Informatica Cloud Data Governance (CDGC)** for data minimization.  \n   - **Protection**: **Informatica Data Privacy Management (DPM)** for policy enforcement.  \n   - **Monitoring**: **Informatica CLAIRE GPT** for detecting unauthorized access.  \n3. **Training**: Conduct mandatory DPDP compliance workshops.  \n\n---\n\n**Next Steps**:  \nPartner with **Informatica experts** to close gaps efficiently.  \nContact **info@datainfa.com** for DPDP implementation support.  \n```",
