gated rights with transparent documentation.  \n\n---\n\n### 3. Data Security Measures (40% Compliance)  \n**Risk Level:** **Critical**  \n*Implications:* Inadequate encryption and access controls increase breach risks.  \n\n**Action Items:**  \n1. Implement **Informatica Dynamic Data Masking** and **Persistent Data Masking** for end-to-end protection.  \n2. Strengthen access controls with **Informatica Cloud Data Access Management (CDAM)** for authentication and logging.  \n3. Enhance monitoring via **real-time alerts** and **automated anomaly detection**.  \n\n---\n\n### 4. Data Breach Notification (16.7% Compliance)  \n**Risk Level:** **Critical**  \n*Implications:* Missed 72-hour reporting windows could result in severe penalties.  \n\n**Action Items:**  \n1. Standardize breach notifications with mandatory details (impact, mitigation steps).  \n2. Automate internal escalation workflows to meet deadlines.  \n\n---\n\n### 5. Data Retention & Erasure (62.5% Compliance)  \n**Risk Level:** **Moderate**  \n*Implications:* Retention of unnecessary data heightens breach risks.  \n\n**Action Items:**  \n1. Automate erasure with **Informatica Cloud Data Integration (CDI)** aligned with **NIST 800-88** standards.  \n\n---\n\n### 6. Cross-Border Data Transfers (50% Compliance)  \n**Risk Level:** **High**  \n*Implications:* Non-adherence to localization norms may trigger regulatory action.  \n\n**Action Items:**  \n1. Use **Informatica Data Engineering Integration** to track data lineage and enforce localization.  \n\n---\n\n### 7. Third-Party Processing (0% Compliance)  \n**Risk Level:** **Critical**  \n*Implications:* Uncontrolled third-party access risks data leaks.  \n\n**Action Items:**  \n1. Develop formal contracts with **audit clauses** and **data protection terms**.  \n2. Extend **Informatica Data Privacy Management** to monitor third-party activities.  \n\n---\n\n## Strategic Recommendations  \n1. **Prioritize High-Risk Areas:** Focus on breach notification, security controls, and third-party oversight.  \n2. **Leverage Automation:** Deploy **Informatica Cloud Data Governance (CDGC)** and **Data Privacy Management** for end-to-end compliance.  \n3. **Upskill Teams:** Train staff on DPDP exemptions and grievance redressal processes.  \n\n---\n\n**Partner with Informatica experts to close gaps efficiently.**  \nContact **info@datainfa.com** for further understanding and DPDP implementation.  \n```",
